      • autonCommandGenerator

        public AutonCommand autonCommandGenerator​(com.pathplanner.lib.PathPlannerTrajectory trajectory,
                                          boolean useAprilTags)
        Generates an AutonCommand object from a PathPlannerTrajectory trajectory. Trajectory's can be loaded from path planner with PathPlanner.loadPath(nameOfYourTrajectory, accelerationAndVelocityConstraints). For an example see generateExamplePathFromFile(). Trajectory's can be made from a list of points by passing in a list of positions: The first Translation2d is a translation that the bot should follow The second parameter is a Rotation2d rotation, the rotation dictates the Spline that is made, which is basically the rotation of the plane that intersects the wheels when the bot gets to a position
        Parameters:
        trajectory - the trajectory from PathPlanner to follow
        useAprilTags - whether or not to use april tags to update odometry during the path
        Returns:
        an AutonCommand object that contains an auton path to run as well as the start and end points
        See Also:
        An explanation on holonomic rotation vs heading. The third parameter is another Rotation2d rotation, this rotation does not affect the path that the bot takes and instead is a holonomic rotation, that dictates the direction that the chassis will face.

      • onTheFlyGenerator

        public AutonCommand onTheFlyGenerator​(edu.wpi.first.math.geometry.Pose2d current,
                                      edu.wpi.first.math.geometry.Pose2d endPoint)
        A method to help with on the fly trajectory generation. As of current it will still update position with april tags however this may need to be changed for better effect in the future.
        Parameters:
        current - the current position of the bot / start position of the trajectory
        endPoint - the end position of the bot / end position of the trajectory
        Returns:
        the Auton command without placement support that will follow the path.

      • loadTrajectory

        public AutonCommand loadTrajectory​(java.lang.String nameOfFile,
                                   boolean requirePlacement)
        loads a PathPlanner trajectory with optional marker support. If you don't want marker support then this command won't require placement subsystems. Any auton commands that are made using this command will use april tags.
        Parameters:
        nameOfFile - the name of the path in PathPlanner
        requirePlacement - whether we should require placement or not
        Returns:
        the generated auton command which requires placement and uses april tags
